The paper discusses self-adaptation in software systems, which falls under the software engineering (cs.SE) category. The approach proposed in the paper involves using utility-driven techniques, which suggests the paper could also be categorized under artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also deals with large dynamic architectures, which could fall under the distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC) category. The self-healing aspect of the paper could also place it under the systems and control (cs.SY) category. Finally, the paper proposes using adaptation rules, which could fall under the programming languages (cs.PL) category.
